{
  "stem": "1799.1",
  "chunk_idx": 9,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 10.8,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 44,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And she saw handwriting on the wall, which was validated by November 9th, I guess-- is when the Crystal Night occurred.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 44,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And my mother and my sister were home.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 44,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "I did not witness it because I was in Berlin at an aunt's house, when they destroyed and burned the synagogue, or the temple and ransacked our home, although they did not burn it.",
      "word_count": 34
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 44,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And that was really the first violent, concerted effort on behalf of the Germans to show Jews-- hey, you guys, you're not wanted here.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 44,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "It was unfortunate that it had to come to that particular demonstration for people to realize that Jews should leave Germany, and-- although a lot of them already had.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 44,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And I would say the exodus of German Jews from, from Germany started in mid-- in the mid '30s. 1935, 1936, 1937 is when people started to, you know, either sell their business or even leave it and leave, knowing that things were not getting any better and more bearable.",
      "word_count": 50
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 45,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "My father was helping these people leave, but he himself felt that he was not in danger.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 45,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Anyway, now he was in jail.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 46,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And his morale was pretty low.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 46,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "He also had a double hernia in that jail, so he had a physical disability.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 46,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And soon my sister-- in December of that year, my sister left to a foster family in England.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 46,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And I remember her coming.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 46,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "By that time, I was in this orphanage where my family sent me in Berlin, [GERMAN SPEECH], which was a well-known, established, old orphanage of very orthodox, and all boys.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 46,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And she came to say goodbye.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 46,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "I didn't really know what was happening.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 46,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "I was still only 13 years old, barely.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 46,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And she said, well, you know, I'll see you.",
      "word_count": 9
    }
  ],
